				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="Liber Militum: Encamisada" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>Liber Militum: Encamisada ventures as the first miniature skirmish wargame in the Liber Militum series, set in the days of the pike and the musket.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Although Liber Militum: Encamisada has as its inspiration from the characteristic skirmishes that arise in the West of Europe, it is perfectly valid for other scenarios of the time. Besides being possible to recreate the endless struggle of Protestants against Catholics in Flanders, we will be able to transport ourselves to the Christian border with the Ottoman Empire, to the Russian steppes or even to the early conquest of America.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;As with Tercios, there is a complete version of the game Liber Militum (forthcoming) and a lighter one, Brevis Editio. The Brevis Editio is fully functional and fully compatible with the other, the rules are the same. Only additional content is added in the Liber Militum: Encamisada&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Factions: In the Liber Militum version it will be possible to choose a Faction for our company. In doing so, the rules of each one will be applied to us, with restrictions and benefits. There are a significant number of Factions, giving us great freedom of customization.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Campaign: Probably the most attractive addition is the possibility of playing in campaign. Different alternative methods are added to manage it with sample maps.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Progression: We have a system of evolution by experience for campaigns, with which we can improve our Captain and the Company.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Scenarios: In the full version we have several extra scenarios: shooting cannons, ambushes or assaults in which civilians participate are some of them.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Multiplayer: Rules are provided for more than two players, including special scenarios.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher (translated)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
